# `make_cv`: Generate Japanese Resume from YAML

[![MIT License](http://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg?style=flat)](LICENSE)

- [kaityo256/yaml_cv](https://github.com/kaityo256/yaml_cv) implemented in Python
- forked from [toritamantaro/yaml_cv_py](https://github.com/toritamantaro/yaml_cv_py)

## Install

```bash
# from pypi
$ pip install yaml_cv_py
# from source
$ git clone https://github.com/eggplants/yaml_cv_py && yaml_cv_py
$ pip install -e .
```

## How to use

```bash
$ make_cv -h
```

```text
usage: make_cv [-h] [-i INPUT] [-s STYLE] [-o OUTPUT] [-V]

Generate japanese resume from yaml file.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help     show this help message and exit
  -i INPUT       set input file path. (default: data.yaml)
  -s STYLE       set style file path. (default: style.yaml)
  -o OUTPUT      set output file path. (default: output.pdf)
  -V, --version  show program's version number and exit
```

```bash
$ make_cv -i data.yaml -s style.txt -o output.pdf
```

